generateClassHeader

public void generateClassHeader(String className,
                                String extendedClassName,
                                String... interfaceNames)
Generates a class header. Pass null to skip the parent class.

Usage: 

 
  generateClassHeader(Foo.class.getSimpleName(),
        HasName.class.getSimpleName,
        "MyGenericInterface<Foo>"
  )

Generated example: 

 public class MyFoo extends Foo implements HasName, MyGenericInterface<Foo> {

Parameters:
extendedClassName - the parent class name
interfaceNames - array of interface names to be implemented

replaceParameters

public static String replaceParameters(String target,
                                       Object... parameters)
Replaces each placeholder of this string that matches a parameter index.

Placeholder format: {int}

Usage:

replaceParameters("{0} int myField = {1};", "private", 20);

Parameters:
target - the string to be replace.
parameters - the replacement parameters
Returns:
the resulting string.

For example:

private int myField = 20;
